sec.p:
The following abbreviations are used herein in the flow modelling approaches:


2D: two-dimensional flow in a rectilinear cascade;

Q2D: quasi-two-dimensional modelling approach applied to an elemental annular (cylindrical) rotor cascade of constant middle radius, by neglecting the radial flow, and assuming the adaptability of 2D cascade correlations;

Q3D: quasi-three-dimensional modelling approach applied to an elemental conical rotor cascade, and assuming the adaptability of 2D cascade correlations;

3D: fully three-dimensional rotor blade passage flow.
